		<td><b>Famiclone legality?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Gamasutra is running an article claiming that <a href="http://www.gamasutra.com/features/20051111/boyd_01.shtml" class="postlink">even with the expiry of key NES patents, Famiclones may not be as legal as some may think</a> because of trademarks and copyrights.
<br />
<br />But the only things that are copyrighted that I can see inside an NES are the circuit board layout (which is all but irrelevant) and the 10NES code in the CIC (which you can just leave unconnected as the toploading NES does). Trademarks are hardly an issue if you make sure to disclaim any confusion: "Compatible with software for Nintendo Entertainment System consoles. (This product is not sponsored or endorsed by Nintendo.)"

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


